params.initialAuthority: The initial authority address for access control

deposit(address,bytes32,bytes32,address,.details: Restricted: only callers granted by `AccessManager` may invoke this function.Validates the destination chain and updates transfer accumulator.Uses either mint/burn or lock/unlock mechanism based on token configuration.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to deposit
params.destAccount: The destination account address (chain-specific format encoded as bytes32)
params.payer: The address whose tokens will be burned/locked

params.depositHash: The deposit hash as returned by `getDepositHash`

getDepositHash((bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,.details: Used for tracking and verification purposes

returns.depositHash: The keccak256 hash of the deposit request

params.count: Maximum number of items to return
params.index: Starting index in the internal set

params.withdrawHash: The withdraw hash as returned by `getWithdrawHash`

returns.withdrawHash: The keccak256 hash of the withdrawal request

params.count: Maximum number of items to return
params.index: Starting index in the internal set

isConsumingScheduledOp().details: Returns true only in the context of a delayed restricted call, at the moment that the scheduled operation is being consumed. Prevents denial of service for delayed restricted calls in the case that the contract performs attacker controlled calls.

pause().details: Restricted: only callers granted by `AccessManager` may invoke this function.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

setAuthority(address).details: Transfers control to a new authority. The caller must be the current authority.

setWithdrawDelay(uint256).details: Restricted: only callers granted by `AccessManager` may invoke this function.

unpause().details: Restricted: only callers granted by `AccessManager` may invoke this function.

withdraw(bytes32,address,address,uint256.details: Restricted: only callers granted by `AccessManager` may invoke this function.Prevents duplicate withdrawals using hash-based tracking

params.amount: The amount of tokens to withdraw
params.nonce: The unique nonce for this withdrawal
params.srcChainKey: The source chain key where the deposit originated
params.token: The token address on this chain

approveWithdraw(bytes32,address,address,.notice: Approve a withdrawal with fee terms

deposit(address,bytes32,bytes32,address,.notice: Deposits tokens to be bridged to another chain

getDepositFromHash(bytes32).notice: Retrieves a stored `Deposit` by its hash

getDepositHash((bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,.notice: Generates a unique hash for a deposit request

getDepositHashes(uint256,uint256).notice: Returns a slice of recorded deposit hashes

getWithdrawApproval(bytes32).notice: Get approval info for a given withdraw hash

getWithdrawFromHash(bytes32).notice: Retrieves a stored `Withdraw` by its hash

getWithdrawHash((bytes32,address,address.notice: Generates a unique hash for a withdrawal request

getWithdrawHashes(uint256,uint256).notice: Returns a slice of recorded withdraw hashes to aid off-chain indexing

lockUnlock().notice: LockUnlock contract instance for handling lock/unlock operations

mintBurn().notice: MintBurn contract instance for handling mint/burn operations

withdraw(bytes32,address,address,uint256.notice: Processes a withdrawal request from another chain

withdrawDelay().notice: Global delay applied between approval and execution of a withdraw
